OL,6,FWhile arrests are made around them,
OL,7,Fcustomers continue to get their nails
OL,8,Fdone by some of the employees.
OL,10,FAt least one those arrested is an
OL,11,Fasylum seeker: they aren't allowed to
OL,12,Fwork while their asylum claims are
OL,13,Fprocessed.
OL,15,FThe third person arrested is the
OL,16,Fmanager of the nail salon, who is
OL,17,Faccused of facilitating illegal work.
